      <div class="msgContentFrame">Since SE is taking the time to make improvements to the UI, I thought I may as well make some suggestions on what I feel would improve it and make it easier to use. <br /> <br />For starters, I'm going to suggest some revisions to the Teleportation menu, since it honestly doesn't feel like it's as intuitive as it could be. So here's an image I cooked up in Photoshop for how I would design the Teleport menu if it were up to me: <br /> <br /><a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v255/snuuj/FFXIV/interface_redesign/teleport_redux_01a.png" title="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v255/snuuj/FFXIV/interface_redesign/teleport_redux_01a.png" rel="external nofollow">http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v255/snuuj/FFXIV/interface_redesign/teleport_redux_01a.png</a> <br /> <br />Not only is this design more intuitive IMO, but it's also more mouse-friendly and requires fewer clicks than the current Teleportation menu. Notice, for example, the addition of a map. Players using a mouse could drag this map around and use it to click on their desired destination directly, without having to go through a bunch of options to get to what they want. <br /> <br />The original menu has been kept on the right side, but in a modified form that displays all sub-options at once, so players don't have to guess about which locations are listed under which region. <br /> <br />Also notice how the Return option has been merged with this menu. Ever since I first saw screenshots of FFXIV's menu, I always thought that Return should be merged into the Teleport menu, as giving it its own option on the main menu felt a bit redundant and slightly confusing. <br /> <br />Feel free to comment and/or make your own UI suggestions. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 16th 2010  1:28am by Rhianu </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 16th 2010  3:44am by Rhianu </span></i></div>
