      <div class="msgContentFrame">I think it would help [them] if you described everything you changed, and why. So they don't have to guess. <br /> <br />It looks very good. <br /> <br />My suggestion is to remove the meaningless confirmation menu when Trading with someone. There are options to &quot;Accept&quot;, &quot;Decline&quot;, and &quot;Cancel&quot;.  <br /> <br />I think it would be much simpler if it is assumed that if you press the &quot;trade&quot; option in the Main Menu you automatically &quot;Accept&quot; the trade. If you don't press it, you &quot;Decline&quot; the trade.  <br /> <br />&quot;Cancel&quot; option should be a part of the Trade menu itself. <br /> <br />With these changes, there wouldn't be a need for yet another menu when trading. <br /> <br />Also as far as your idea goes, instead of linking the map with the teleport menu, you could simply make it so you can also teleport from the map itself with a mouse or even gamepad? Or you could even combine the &quot;Map&quot; and &quot;Teleport&quot; menus, but I don't know how it would be best accomplished without taking away too much space from the map. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 16th 2010  9:33am by Hyanmen </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>SE: <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">We don't really want to compete against World of Warcraft or for example the new Star Wars MMO.</div></div> <br /></div></div>
