      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Hyanmen wrote:</div><div class="orig">There are options to &quot;Accept&quot;, &quot;Decline&quot;, and &quot;Cancel&quot;.</div></div> <br />Yeah, that right there is honestly pretty redundant. =/ <br /> <br /><i>&quot;Do you want to trade?&quot;</i> <br /> <br />That's a yes or no question. There are only two possible answers to a yes or no question, yet this menu throws three options at us for no apparent reason, which is confusing. <br /> <br />I mean, what's the difference between &quot;Decline&quot; and &quot;Cancel&quot;? They might function differently in the underlying code, but clicking either one would terminate the trade process. So since both options do the exact same thing, one of them should be eliminated (even though the code for each one may be different). <br /> <br />Mistakes like this happen when you let your programmers do your design work. =/ <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 16th 2010  1:39am by Rhianu </span></i></div>
